import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the deceased persons?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='neighborhood', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of incidents by neighborhood?', wrap=True)
    return plt;
